The 35-year-old woman was gunned down at her home in front of her two children on Monday night. CAPE TOWN - Police have launched an investigation into the murder of a Lwandle mother who was shot dead at her home. The 35-year-old woman was gunned down in front of her two children on Monday night. Two men are believed to have entered the house and robbed them at gunpoint. The police's Frederick van Wyk said: We can confirm that cases of murder and house robbery are under investigation. The two suspects fatally shot the woman and stole of her belongings. 